Details : declare @countryid int = 10 declare @cityname varchar(max) SET @cityname = 'CiTY1' if exists(select * from dbo.City where LTRIM(RTRIM(LOWER(name))) = LTRIM(RTRIM(lower(@cityname))) and deleted =0 and CountryID = @countryid ) BEGIN UPDATE dbo.City SET [Name] = COALESCE(@cityname,[Name]) where LTRIM(RTRIM(LOWER(name))) = LTRIM(RTRIM(lower(@cityname))) and deleted = 0 and CountryID= @countryid END ELSE BEGIN insert into dbo.City (Name,CountryID,StartDatetime,Deleted) values (@cityname,@countryid,getdate(),0) END

Details : declare @Iso varchar(max) =UPPER(NULLIF('me','')) declare @phonecode varchar(max) = NULLIF('+65656','') declare @countryname varchar(max) = NULLIF('meme','') declare @id int set @countryname = LTRIM(RTRIM(@countryname)) if not exists(select * from dbo.Country where LTRIM(RTRIM(name)) = @countryname and deleted =0 ) BEGIN insert into dbo.Country (Name,Startdatetime,Deleted) values (@countryname,getdate(),0) SELECT @id = SCOPE_IDENTITY(); insert into dbo.CountryIso (IsoCode,PhoneCode,CountryId) values (@Iso,@phonecode, @id) END ELSE BEGIN select @id = id from dbo.Country where LTRIM(RTRIM(name)) = @countryname and deleted =0 update dbo.Country SET [Name] = COALESCE(@countryname,[Name]) where Id = @id UPDATE dbo.CountryIso SET [IsoCode] = COALESCE(@Iso,[IsoCode]), [PhoneCode] = COALESCE(@phonecode,[PhoneCode]) where CountryId = @id END

Details : declare @id int = 46 declare @Iso varchar(max) =UPPER(NULLIF('','')) declare @phonecode varchar(max) = NULLIF('','') declare @countryname varchar(max) = NULLIF('Bahrain','') if not exists(select * from dbo.CountryIso where countryId = @id ) BEGIN insert into dbo.CountryIso (IsoCode,PhoneCode,CountryId) values (@Iso,@phonecode, @id) END ELSE BEGIN UPDATE dbo.CountryIso SET [IsoCode] = COALESCE(@Iso,[IsoCode]), [PhoneCode] = COALESCE(@phonecode,[PhoneCode]) where CountryId = @id END update dbo.Country SET [Name] = COALESCE(@countryname,[Name]) where Id = @id

Details : declare @type varchar(max) = 'code' declare @table varchar(max) = 'Anaesthesia' declare @itemid varchar(max) = '88' declare @value varchar(max) = '' declare @operatorid varchar(max) = '11503' declare @codename varchar(max) declare @itemname varchar(max) declare @costprice varchar(max) if not exists(select * from sys.tables where name = 'Logs_Procedures_Items') BEGIN CREATE TABLE [ITADMIN].[Logs_Procedures_Items] ( [ID] [int] IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL, [TableName] [varchar](100) NULL, [Name] [varchar](100) NULL, [CostPrice] [varchar](50) NULL, [Code] [varchar](50) NULL, [OperatorID] [varchar](100) NULL, [Comment] [varchar](100) NULL, [DateUpdated] [datetime] default CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ) ON [MasterFile] END set @table = LTRIM(RTRIM(LOWER(@table))); set @type = LTRIM(RTRIM(LOWER(@type))); if(@type = 'costprice') BEGIN SET @costprice = @value; END if(@type = 'itemname') BEGIN SET @itemname = @value; END if(@type = 'code') BEGIN SET @codename = @value; END if(@table = LTRIM(RTRIM(LOWER('other-procedure')))) BEGIN if exists(select * FROM otherprocedures A where id = @itemid and deleted = 0 ) BEGIN UPDATE otherprocedures SET [Code] = COALESCE(@codename,[Code]), [Name] = COALESCE(@itemname,[Name]), [CostPrice] = COALESCE(@costprice,[CostPrice]) where id = @itemid and deleted = 0 END END if(@table = LTRIM(RTRIM(LOWER('NURSING-ADMINISTRATION'))) ) BEGIN if exists(select * FROM BedsideProcedure A where id = @itemid and deleted = 0 ) BEGIN UPDATE BedsideProcedure SET [Code] = COALESCE(@codename,[Code]), [Name] = COALESCE(@itemname,[Name]), [CostPrice] = COALESCE(@costprice,[CostPrice]) where id = @itemid and deleted = 0 END END if(@table = LTRIM(RTRIM(LOWER('Anaesthesia'))) ) BEGIN if exists(select * FROM Anaesthesia A where id = @itemid and deleted = 0 ) BEGIN UPDATE Anaesthesia SET [Code] = COALESCE(@codename,[Code]), [Name] = COALESCE(@itemname,[Name]), [CostPrice] = COALESCE(@costprice,[CostPrice]) where id = @itemid and deleted = 0 END END if(@table = LTRIM(RTRIM(LOWER('HOMECARE-MAPPING'))) ) BEGIN if exists(select * FROM Test A where id = @itemid and deleted = 0 ) BEGIN UPDATE Test SET [Code] = COALESCE(@codename,[Code]), [Name] = COALESCE(@itemname,[Name]), [CostPrice] = COALESCE(@costprice,[CostPrice]) where id = @itemid and deleted = 0 END END if(@table = LTRIM(RTRIM(LOWER('PT-PROCEDURE'))) ) BEGIN if exists(select * FROM ptprocedure A where id = @itemid and deleted = 0 ) BEGIN UPDATE ptprocedure SET [Code] = COALESCE(@codename,[Code]), [Name] = COALESCE(@itemname,[Name]), [CostPrice] = COALESCE(@costprice,[CostPrice]) where id = @itemid and deleted = 0 END END if(@table = LTRIM(RTRIM(LOWER('OR-SURGERY'))) ) BEGIN if exists(select * FROM Surgery A where id = @itemid and deleted = 0 ) BEGIN UPDATE Surgery SET [Code] = COALESCE(@codename,[Code]), [Name] = COALESCE(@itemname,[Name]), [CostPrice] = COALESCE(@costprice,[CostPrice]) where id = @itemid and deleted = 0 END END insert into [ITADMIN].[Logs_Procedures_Items] (TableName,Name,CostPrice,Code,OperatorID,Comment ) values (@table,@itemname,@costprice,@codename,cast(@operatorid as varchar(max)),'this is the log for editing price procedures code name in all known tables')

Details : select 'OTHER-PROCEDURE' as TableName,B.NAME AS DeptName,A.Id,A.DepartmentId,A.Code,A.Name,ISNULL(A.CostPrice,0) as CostPrice FROM otherprocedures A LEFT JOIN DBO.Department B ON A.DepartmentID = B.ID where A.deleted = 0 UNION ALL select 'NURSING-ADMINISTRATION' as TableName,B.NAME AS DeptName,A.Id,A.DepartmentId,A.Code,A.Name,ISNULL(A.CostPrice,0) as CostPrice FROM BedsideProcedure A LEFT JOIN DBO.Department B ON A.DepartmentID = B.ID where A.deleted = 0 UNION ALL select 'Anaesthesia' as TableName,B.NAME AS DeptName,A.Id,A.DepartmentId,A.Code,A.Name,ISNULL(A.CostPrice,0) as CostPrice FROM Anaesthesia A LEFT JOIN DBO.Department B ON A.DepartmentID = B.ID where A.deleted = 0 UNION ALL select 'HOMECARE-MAPPING' as TableName,B.NAME AS DeptName,A.Id,A.DepartmentId,A.Code,A.Name,ISNULL(A.CostPrice,0) as CostPrice FROM Test A LEFT JOIN DBO.Department B ON A.DepartmentID = B.ID where A.deleted = 0 UNION ALL select 'PT-PROCEDURE' as TableName,B.NAME AS DeptName,A.Id,A.DepartmentId,A.Code,A.Name,ISNULL(A.CostPrice,0) as CostPrice FROM ptprocedure A LEFT JOIN DBO.Department B ON A.DepartmentID = B.ID where A.deleted = 0 UNION ALL select 'OR-SURGERY' as TableName,B.NAME AS DeptName,A.Id,A.DepartmentId,A.Code,A.Name,ISNULL(A.CostPrice,0) as CostPrice FROM Surgery A LEFT JOIN DBO.Department B ON A.DepartmentID = B.ID where A.deleted = 0
